That their doctrine ſet downe (as is before ſaid) doth yeeld this anſwer, they that are acquainted with the writings of the learned in the Popiſh Church will witneſſe with me: and 
                     •
                   doe make demonſtration thereof on this wiſe;

This branch doth appertaine to Pred
                     •
                  ſtination, for it concerneth mans ordering vnto his laſt end, and perfection. The other ſixe, belong not thereto; for they ſpeake of mans being, and the cauſes thereof, and things pertaining thereto. They haue not a word of ordering man, to any end. If this ſeuenth branch bee framed according to Art, it will ſtand thus;
